│ THOUGHT: The crash is due to TreeEntry::getOperand asserting when queried with an operand index that exceeds the current size of the Operands vector during SLP costing/building  │
│ in certain reduction scenarios. A safe fix is to guard both the non-const and const getOperand accessors: if OpIdx is out of range, return an empty operand list/ArrayRef instead │
│ of asserting. This preserves correctness (no invalid bundling) and avoids the abort. I'll patch SLPVectorizer.cpp accordingly, rebuild opt, verify the reproducer no longer       │
│ crashes, and submit the patch.                                                                                                                                                    │
│                                                                                                                                                                                   │
