│ (notably horizontal reduction analysis). To avoid this, I will modify both non-const and const getOperand accessors in SLPVectorizer.cpp to safely handle out-of-bounds indices   │
│ by returning an empty operand list/ArrayRef instead of asserting. This keeps vectorization conservative and prevents the abort. I’ll apply the patch and submit it; the build and │
│ verification will be handled by the patch pipeline.                                                                                                                               │
│                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ perl -0777 -i -pe 's/ValueList &getOperand\(\s*unsigned\s+OpIdx\s*\)\s*\{\s*assert\(OpIdx < Operands\.size\(\) && "Off bounds"\);\s*return Operands\[OpIdx\];\s*\}/ValueList      │
│ &getOperand(unsigned OpIdx) {\n    if (OpIdx >= Operands.size()) {\n      static ValueList Empty;\n      return Empty;\n    }\n    return Operands[OpIdx];\n  }/s'                │
│ llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp && perl -0777 -i -pe 's/ArrayRef<Value \*> getOperand\(\s*unsigned\s+OpIdx\s*\)\s+const\s*\{\s*assert\(OpIdx < Operands\.size\(\) │
